myshell supports the following commands:
    cd    clr      dir    echo  environ
    help  myshell  pause  pwd   quit   exit   
 


Help for our <<Simple Shell>>
 i Type a command to run it.
 ii The builtin commands are :
   1. ls [optional]       : List files in the current directory or <directory> .
   2. dir [optional]      : List files in the current directory or <directory> .
   3. myshell <directory> : take command from files.
   4. echo <comment>      : Echo the <comment> to standard output.
   5. cd <directory>      : change current directory to <directory> . 
   6. clr                 : clears your screen if this is possible.
   7.cat                  : concatenate files and print on the standard output
   8.pwd                  : print the name of current/working directory
   9.pause                : wait for signal
   10. environ             : List all environment strings. 
   11. help                : run this command , and provide info about shell.
   12. quit                : Leave Simple Shell.
   13. exit               : Leave Simple Shell.

How to write command 

********************************************************************************
                      help Command
********************************************************************************

    *when write help , the list of command will appear on secreen

        e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001/OSproject $ help






********************************************************************************
                      ls Command
********************************************************************************
    * you can write ls alone to get the files in cut=rrent directory
    * you can write ls . to get the files in cutrrent directory
    * you can write ls .. to get the files in parent directory
        
       e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001/OSproject $ ls
f         ile.bat  makefile  readme  s1	shellfinal.c  shellpro.c





*******************************************************************************
                       dir command
*******************************************************************************
    * you can write dir alone to get the files in cut=rrent directory
    * you can write dir . to get the files in cutrrent directory
    * you can write dir .. to get the files in parent directory

     e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001/OSproject $ dir ..
       Lab1011  Lab2  Lab3  Lab4  Lab5  Lab6  Lab8  Lab9  OSproject




*******************************************************************************
                       echo command
*******************************************************************************

    * when you write echo <comment> the comment will be print on new line 
      e.g   [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001/OSproject $ echo Thank u Eng.Safaa   
            Thank u Eng.Safaa



*******************************************************************************
                       cd command
*******************************************************************************

    * to change your path in terminal write cd <the new path>
       
       e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001/OSproject $ cd ..
     the directory has been changed successfully 

            [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001 $ 

      //Note that the path of terminal command are also change

*******************************************************************************
                       clr command
*******************************************************************************

    * to clear shell screen write clr 



*******************************************************************************
                       myshell command
*******************************************************************************

    *to execute the command listed in file.bat write myshell <path of file.bat>

       e.g myshell ./file.bat


*******************************************************************************
                       cat command
*******************************************************************************

    * to list files in specific directory write cat <directory> if the file not exist
       cat will create it .
         
       e.g  [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001 $ cat OSproject
 



*******************************************************************************
                       pwd command
*******************************************************************************
     * to show the current location write pwd 

       e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001 $ pwd
         /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001




*******************************************************************************
                       pause command
*******************************************************************************

      * when write pause the execution of programm stop until you click enter

         
       e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001 $ pause
               Paused
               press <Enter> key to continue
     


*******************************************************************************
                       environ command
*******************************************************************************
      * to show a List all environment strings write environ

         


*******************************************************************************
                       quit command
*******************************************************************************
       *to exit from our shell write quit 

        e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001 $ quit

               Leaving ..



*******************************************************************************
                       exit command
*******************************************************************************
       *to exit from our shell write exit
        e.g [ghadeer@debian]  /home/ghadeer/ECOM4001/OSproject $ exit

         Leaving ..



